{
  "texts": [
    "For any BAO A and φ ∈ L(Φ, I), φ is satisfiable over A iff φ is satisfiable over A g.Proof.",
    "The left-to-right direction is given by Theorem 5.31.5.",
    "From right to left, if φ is satisfied in a possibility model M based on A g, then by Lemma 5.32, it is satisfied in the possibility model (M -g) g, in which case by Theorem 5.31.3 it is satisfied in the algebraic model M -g based on A.Not only is every BAO semantically equivalent to its general filter frame, but also homomorphisms between BAOs transform into possibility morphisms between their general filter frames as follows.Theorem 5.34 (From BAO-homomorphisms to Possibility Morphisms II).",
    "For any BAOs A and A ′ and BAO-homomorphism h:A ′ → A, define h g: A g → A ′ g by h g (X) = h -1 [X].",
    "Then:1. h g is a p-morphism;2. if h is surjective, then h g is a strong embedding;3. if h is injective, then h g is surjective;4. as a function from A f to A ′ f, h g still satisfies parts 1-3; if f:A → A is the identity map on A, then f g is the identity map on A g; 6. for any BAO-homomorphisms f: A → B and g: B → C, (g • f) g = f g • g g.Proof."
  ]
}